              <div class="footnote">
                <p>*Average life-of-loan savings of $17,320 is based on a study of refinance loans originated between April
                  2016 and June 2017 that paid off underlying Navient private and federal student loans. The savings calculation
                  assumes the following: the average refinance balance is $50,000; all payments are made on time; and no
                  loans are prepaid. Further, the savings is based on the difference of the weighted average repayment period
                  and the weighted average interest rate associated with the underlying Navient loans compared to the weighted
                  averages of the refinance loans. The calculation excludes consumers who selected a refinance loan repayment
                  period greater than the weighted average repayment period on their underlying loans.
                </p>
